This folder contains tools to request seismic data in SAC format and prepare the data for processing with CAP.
For older instructions about using iris_tools.py see
~/REPOSITORIES/GEOTOOLS/python_util/sandbox/util_cap/README_iris_tools 

Tool to get SAC data from IRIS
iris_tools.py

Tool to get SAC data from LLNL database
llnl_tool.py

Example 1. Python script to get data for the Iniskin event
--------
import obspy
import iris_tools
import copy
from obspy.clients.fdsn import Client

c = Client("IRIS")

otime = obspy.UTCDateTime("2016-01-24T10:30:29")

cat = c.get_events(starttime = otime-10, endtime = otime+10)
network='*'
iris_tools.run_get_waveform(ev=cat[0], min_dist=0, max_dist=200, 
        before = 20, after = 600,
        network=network, channel='BH*', samp_freq=20.0, rotate=True,
        output_cap_weight_file=True, remove_response=True,
        detrend=True, demean=True, output_event_info=True,
                     pre_filt=(0.005, 0.006, 5.0, 10.0)
                     )

--------

